  <h1 id="intro">Introduction to Falls</h1>
  <h5>Falls or Falling is one of the main causes of disability and morbidity in older adults. Every year, more than one third of people older than 65 years fall, and half of these falls are recurrent.</h5>
  <h5>As you age, the risk of falling increases, especially with the presence of a cognitive impairment or a history of previous falls, where the risk may doubles or even triples.</h5>
  <h5>Among Canadians 65 years and older, falls account for 85% of injury-related hospital admissions (<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3135440/">Al-Aama, 2011</a>).</h5>


