    <h1 id="risk">Risks & Causes of Falls</h1>
    <h5> Several risk factors have already been identified in the literature.</h5>
    <h5><img src="images/atrophy.png" alt=""> Loss of Muscular Mass (Muscle Atrophy)</h5>
    <h5> <img src="images/ortho.jpeg" alt=""> Blood pressure dropping from position change</h5>
    <h5><img src="images/Medizzy.png" alt=""> Medications causing side effects such as Dizzines (mainly Diabete & Hypertension medications)</h5>
    <h5> <img src="images/hazards.png" alt=""> Safety hazards (such as rugs, cables, shoes, wet floor ...etc.)</h5>


    <h1 id="complic">Complications of Falls</h1>
    <h5>Falls are a frequent and serious health problem with some devastating consequences.</h5>
    <h5><img src="images/hospit.png" alt=""> Prolonged hospitalization (average 9 days longer)</h5>
    <h5><img src="images/braininj.png" alt=""> Head injuries (brain bleeding)</h5>
    <h5><img src="images/fracture.png" alt=""> Fractures (Bones)</h5>
    <h5><img src="images/strain.png" alt=""> Sprains/strains (Ligaments/tendons)</h5>
    <h5><img src="images/fear.jpeg" alt=""> Fear of falling </h5>
    <h5><img src="images/canot.png" alt=""> Loss of self confidence</h5>


    <h1 id="prevent">Falls Prevention</h1>
    <h5>Falls can be prevented through a variety of evidence-based interventions that can be simple or complex.</h5>
    <h5><img src="images/rightshoes.png" alt=""> Wear well-fitted shoes with good grip (avoid High Heels)</h5>
    <h5><img src="images/lithome.png" alt=""> Make sure the room is well-lit (clear of tripping hazards)</h5>
    <h5><img src="images/assist.png" alt=""> Use assistive devices if needed (cane, walker, wheelchair ...etc.)</h5>
    <h5><img src="images/railing.png" alt=""> Keep hands free to be able to hold onto railings</h5>
    <h5><img src="images/mat.png" alt=""> Replace carpets with non slip mat </h5>
    <h5><img src="images/slipmat.png" alt=""> Place non slip mats in bathtub and bathroom floor as well</h5>
    <h5><img src="images/sitedge.png" alt=""> Sit on the edge of the bed for 1 minute before standing </h5>
    <h5><img src="images/head of the bed.jpeg" alt=""> Sleep with head slightly elevated</h5>
    <h5><img src="images/icegripcane.jpeg" alt=""> If using cane, buy an ice grip tip </h5>
    <h5><img src="images/gripons.png" alt=""> Use grip-ons (ice cleats). Always try to avoid snow or ice!</h5>

